article.headline: Alabama State 61, Troy 48
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Kevin Spicer scored 16 points and Herbert Warren Ralfeal Golden each added 12 points, leading Alabama State to a 61-48 victory over Troy on Tuesday night. Spicer shot 4-of-5 from the field and was 8-of-10 in free throw attempts. Warren hit 5-of-5 shots and Golden was 2-of-3 from 3-point range for the Hornets (2-5). Eddie Baker, Bobby Dixon and Richard Damus each scored 10 points for Troy (1-8). Spicer tied the game 40-40 with a tip-in at 5:46 mark. The Hornets regained the lead on a Warren floater that sparked at 10-0 run. The Hornets, who led 23-22 at halftime, outrebounded Troy 35-20.
